```julia
function add_yearmonth(df)
    df[:ym] = Dates.format.(df[:dt], "yyyyMM");
end
```

This function `add_yearmonth` takes a DataFrame `df` as input. It creates a new column `ym` and uses the `Dates.format` function to extract year and month from the `dt` column, formatting them as "yyyymm". The `.()` syntax is used for broadcasting the operation to each element in the column.
